Package com.natwest.opendata.service

Class BranchesServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.natwest.opendata.service.BranchesServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseOpenDataService, BranchesService
    public class BranchesServiceImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements BranchesService
    The BranchesServiceImpl class is an implementation of BranchesSerivce Interface. All methods pertaining to Branch functionalities are implemented in this class.

    BranchesServiceImpl is public class, an implementation, that get exposed to the developers or consumer of this SDK. Because BranchesServiceImpl is public class, its methods are visible and can be consumed.

    Here are some more examples of how strings can be used: 

         Recommended way to use:
     OpenDataService openDataService=new OpenDataService(Environment.PROD);
     BranchesService branchesService=openDataService.getBranchesService();
     branchesService.getAllData();

    The class BranchesSerivceImpl includes methods for consuming various functionalities pertaining to Branches open data SDK, for example getting all Branches data as list, filtering Branches based on properties etc.

    Exposed Methods:

    • getBranchesByFilter
    • getAllData
    • exportAllDataAsCSV
    Since:
    1.0
